<item>
            <title>[HTTPCLIENT-166] waitForResponse is using busy wait</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HTTPCLIENT-166</link>
                <project id="12310360" key="HTTPCLIENT">HttpComponents HttpClient</project>
                        <description>In HttpConnection, the method waitForResponse is using busywait, instead of &lt;br/&gt;
blocking until the response is arriving.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
Is this on purpose, or shouldn&amp;#39;t it handle this by blocking instead ??</description>
                <environment>Operating System: All&lt;br/&gt;
Platform: All</environment>
            <key id="12333725">HTTPCLIENT-166</key>
            <summary>waitForResponse is using busy wait</summary>
                <type id="1" iconUrl="https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/issuetypes/bug.png">Bug</type>
                                <priority id="3" iconUrl="https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/priorities/major.png">Major</priority>
